commitResults.messageBody:
The current UI package structure is not intuitive and extensible.
OOP principles are violated as the the enclosing component is responsible
for loading the subcomponents of their child's UI. This makes it confusing
to the programmer. For example, the MainWindow class is the responsibility
of loading each tab into the TabPane.

The java files are also all thrown into the same package in the ui package
which makes it difficult to navigate and organise the ui components according
to their hierachy.

This commit refactors the UI package structure to be more intuitive and
extensible. The following changes were made:
1. Renamed ResultDisplay to CommandLog
1. Abstracted out TabsPane into the TabsHolder class
1. Moved all UI parts into their own subpackages
1. Moved UI test files to the same package as the UI files they test

With this refactor, the UI package structure is now more intuitive and extensible.

CommandResult and CommandException now has a UiAction attribute.
UiAction is an interface that has a method `execute(MainWindow mainWindow)`
that tells the UI what to do after the command.

1. Refactored the CommandResult to use UiAction instead of exit and help boolean attributes.
1. All ClientCommands now switches to client tab after execution.
1. All ProjectCommands now switches to project tab after execution.

commitResults.messageBody: Fix wrong validation of updated project and client

Previously, selecting entity with mouse will unfocus on the command box.
With the way `UiEventManager` was implemented, the `CommandBox` will
be brought into focus whenever a key is pressed. This led to `Enter`
refocusing on command box to the start of line, which somehow led to
the whole box being highlighted.

This has been fix now as every key press will send refocus to command box
if not already focused and position the caret at the end of the text only
when refocusing is done. This prevents the highlighting of the whole command box
when refocusing on command box.

Previously, selecting eneity with mouse in command box and pressing enter
creates a odd behaviour where the command box is filled with reference before
quickly being cleared again. This has been fix by creating a `EnterKey` key
binds which forces input submission when enter is pressed regardless of focus.
This allows the selection of entity made with mouse to be utilised despite
a selection with mouse unfocuses from the command box.
